@node Main "Amiga Foundation Classes: explain_exception"



                   ** Explain_Exception  - Original By Fabio Rotondo **

                       * Part of the Amiga Foundation Classes *

                @{" Author's Info " link "author"}  @{" Amiga Foundation Classes " LINK "AFC.Guide/main"}  @{" History " LINK "explain_exception_History"}

       REQUIRES: AmigaE version needs "tools/exceptions"



           NAME: explain_exception(v=0)

       SYNOPSIS: VOID explain_exception(LONG v=0)

    DESCRIPTION: This function helps you to debug your program.
                 Using this program you can "translate" the error Raise()d
                 by a method inside an AFC class into a message sent to the
                 consolle.
                 It is incredibly easy and handy to use.


          INPUT: v            - (Optional) Exception value.
                                If it is omitted, it will return the
                                current exception.


        RESULTS: NONE.


       SEE ALSO:

@endnode

